  "text": "The main result in [CITATION_1] states that for ij = 12, 23, 31 there exists a positive stretching factor kij ∈ N such that g(kijλij, (kij d) n , (kij d) n ) = 0. Let k be the least common multiple of k12, k23, k31. Then we have for ij = 12, 23, 31",
